cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it deals with the deployment and management of wireless backhaul networks for 5G wireless networks. It may also belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category as it considers the optimization of wireless backhaul routes based on time-variant wireless channels. Additionally, it could be categorized under Systems and Control (cs.SY) as it proposes an optimization algorithm for the deployment and management of wireless backhaul networks. Multimedia (cs.MM) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) are less likely sub-categories as they are not directly related to the optimization of wireless backhaul networks.
